1. Fulbright Foreign Student Program
Deadline: August 1, 2025 (varies by country)
Focus: Graduate study, research, and teaching opportunities
Eligibility: International students
Website: https://foreign.fulbrightonline.org/
Funding: Covers tuition, living expenses, health insurance, and travel

2. Marie Skłodowska-Curie Actions Postdoctoral Fellowships
Deadline: September 10, 2025
Focus: Research in any discipline in Europe
Eligibility: PhD holders with max 8 years experience
Website: MSCA Fellowships
Duration: 1-2 years

3. Newton International Fellowships
Deadline: March 18, 2025
Focus: Research in UK institutions
Eligibility: Early-career researchers outside the UK
Website: https://ec.europa.eu/research/mariecurieactions/

Funding: £24,000 per annum tax-free subsistence allowance plus research expenses

4. DAAD Research Grants
Deadline: August 29, 2025 (varies by country)
Focus: Research in Germany
Eligibility: International doctoral candidates and postdocs
Website: https://www.daad.de/en/study-and-research-in-germany/scholarships/
Duration: 1-10 months depending on project type

5. Japan Society for the Promotion of Science Fellowships
Deadline: June 6, 2025
Focus: Research in Japan
Eligibility: PhD holders from around the world
Website: https://www.jsps.go.jp/english/e-fellow/
Duration: 1-24 months depending on fellowship category

6. Wellcome Trust International Fellowships
Deadline: Variable deadlines (check against respective projects on website)
Focus: Health research
Eligibility: Early to mid-career researchers
Website: https://wellcome.org/grant-funding
Funding: Salary and research expenses

7. Alexander von Humboldt Foundation Research Fellowship
Deadline: Rolling (outcomes in June and December 2025)
Focus: Research in Germany
Eligibility: Postdoctoral researchers worldwide
Website: https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/en/apply/sponsorship-programmes/humboldt-research-fellowship
Duration: 6-24 months

# 8. Rhodes Global Scholarships
Deadline: July 31, 2025
Focus: Graduate study at Oxford University
Eligibility: Outstanding young leaders worldwide
Website: https://www.rhodeshouse.ox.ac.uk/scholarships/the-rhodes-scholarship/
Funding: Full costs including tuition and stipend

10. Vanier Canada Graduate Scholarships
Deadline: To be updated
Focus: Doctoral studies in Canada
Eligibility: International and Canadian students
Website: https://vanier.gc.ca/
Funding: $50,000 CAD per year for three years

## 11. The French Institutes for Advanced Study Fellowship Programme
Deadline: July 16, 2025
Focus: Innovative research projects in France.
Eligibility: PhD + 2 years of research experience
Website: https://www.fias-fp.eu/fellowships/call-applications
Funding: A net living allowance (equivalent to take-home pay) of min. €2,200 per month, an individual research and training budget equivalent to €2,500 per year, travel expenses
